@NODE Source_files "Source files"

          You  need  to  recompile them SAS C V6.3 and (HW)RCS.  If you
          want to recompile the AXSh version, you need the source files
          of  AXSh.lib  to  compile  a  resident and register parameter
          version  of  the  axsh.lib.   If  you  want  to recompile the
          MultiUserFileSystem  you  need  the  include  files from MUFS
          distribution.    If   you   want   to   recompile   the  with
          netsupport.library   you   need   the   include   files  from
          NetSupport.library distribution.

          @{fg fill}Attention!!!@{fg text}


          If you change something,

          a) please inform me, so that I can submit your changes in the
             "official" distribution.

          b)  check  your changes in as branches !  It is easier for me
              to merge them.


@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"

          Version 1.0 (16 Nov 1993)
          -------------------------

                       »»»»»»»»»» INITIAL RELEASE «««««««««««

          Version 2.0 (1 Dez 1993)
          -------------------------

           o Rewritten the routines for error messages (see @{" Config options " Link Config_options})

           o Dillon styled logfile output changed

           o Netsupport.library is now used

           o some changes in source files (you should not notice)
             and some little changes in output messages

           o improved  %-address support

           o fixed a bug in installer script (SMPath was invalid)

           o should now works with PGPMIP (great work Peter Simons !)

           o improved guide file

           o message id is now unique (using uulib:seq)

           o ~ in :include: statement for aliasing will be expanded
             to home dir of the program's caller

           o in the CNews styled logfile there is logged the
             delivering time of the mail (evaluated from the Date: Header)

           o there were be problems with the logfiles and
             Return-Receipt-To: if there are more than one
             addresses in To:/Cc:/Bcc: lines. Only the first
             address were used. This is now fixed.

           o fixed some enforcer hits in aliasing routines

           o fixed a bug in finding a host in path file (Thanks to Hans Maurer 
)

           o fixed error in installer script (SMPath was invalid)

           o fixed error in passwd routines in the Getty version

           o timezone information now works

@ENDNODE

